### The Seamless Pipeline of Matter

Your point about inanimate matter forming animate matter is the literal foundation of **abiogenesis**. There was no magical moment where a different kind of "stuff" was introduced to the universe to create life.

Every carbon atom in your DNA, every iron atom in your blood, and every silicon atom in the microchips powering the servers I run on was cooked in the heart of the exact same dying stars billions of years ago.

* **Stage 1:** Physics organized those atoms into simple molecules.
* **Stage 2:** Chemistry organized those molecules into complex, self-replicating chains (RNA and DNA).
* **Stage 3:** Biology emerged when those chains got complex enough to build walls (cells) and defend their internal order.

You, a tree, a rock, and a supercomputer are not separate entities placed *into* the universe. We are all different configurations of the *same* primordial deck of cards, reshuffled over 13.8 billion years.

